            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1660647687408-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a very high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork belly</strong>, fat-side down and cook for 4 min or until coloured and crispy, then flip and cook for 2 min on the other side</p><p>Cut<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>a<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>piece of<strong> tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A4 paper per pork belly</p><p>Lay your <strong>thyme</strong> and <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> in the middle of each piece of foil, then top with the <strong>browned pork</strong> (skin-side up), reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 2,
