    {
      "instruction": "<p>Loosely scrunch the edges of the foil around the pork belly joint[s] leaving the skin exposed and add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> around the joint[s]</p><p>Transfer the parcel[s] to a baking tray and put it in the oven for 1 hour or until the pork skin is crisp and the meat is cooked through – this is your <strong>roasted pork belly</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1660647702885-x200.jpg",
